a.xlink:title: Time span defined by a start date and time, and an end date and time.
Instruction given by an account holder to an account servicer to make regular transfers on given dates to the same beneficiary.
Instruction to pay an amount of money to an ultimate beneficiary, on behalf of an originator. This instruction may have to be forwarded several times to complete the settlement chain.
Statistical data related to the price change of a security.
Performance factors of the investment fund / fund class.
The status of an instruction, advice or request.
Characteristics related to the price of the security.

Provides information about the alternatives available to an account owner when participating to a corporate action event. This is defined at a general level without looking at the specificities of the securities balances.

The definition of the securities proceeds for a corporate action in generic terms; that is, before applying it to specific securities holding. An example would be the definition of a bonus rights issue where all the information will be given in general on a per share basis.
Period defining the last date for which an action will be accepted and the date on which the suspension will be released and normal processing will resume.
Set of parameters used to calculate an interest amount.
Specifies the conditions under which securities can be acquired as part of a corporate action.
Form of lawsuit in which a group of shareholders collectively bring a claim to court, mainly because it would be too expensive for each individual shareholder to launch their own lawsuit.
An event determined by a corporation's board of directors, that changes the existing corporate capital structure or financial condition.
Financial instruments evidencing moneys owed by the issuer to the holder on terms as specified.
Conversion exchange of securities, generally convertible bonds or preferred equities, into another form of securities, usually common equities.
Characteristics related to the yield.
Period of time details related to the tax payment.

Record of transactions in specific types of assets, maintained by a servicing party on behalf of one or more owning parties. Business relationship between an account servicer and one or more account owners.
Contractual details related to an agreement between parties.
Arrangements for delivery of invoiced products and/or services.
General information about an invoice, such as number, issue date date and monetary amounts.
Formal document used to record a fact and used as proof of the fact, in the context of a commercial trade transaction.
Valuation information of the portfolio.
Set of integrated applications that provides centralised services such as clearing, netting, reconciliation, trading and/or settlement.
Restriction on capability or operations allowed.
Operation on a bank account. It may be limited in time, amount or type of operation.
Value used for risk containment in a system or towards counterparts. The limit may be a current limit or a default limit.
Unique and unambiguous way to identify a party
Information regarding an enumerated code list and its owner.
Distributions in cash and/or securities following a corporate event.
Partial or full coverage of amounts by a party other than the debtor.
Security which forms a component of another security, for example, underlying.
Established constraints under which a market operates
Characteristics and conditions by which a borrower can exchange one type of financial instrument for another.
Information that locates and identifies a specific address.
Describes the reason and terms for early partial or total redemption, amortisation or extension of an issue.
Defines the link between the accounts held with a market infrastructure.
Modification on the value of goods and / or services. For example: rebate, discount.
Unique and unambiguous identifier of a security, assigned under a formal or proprietary identification scheme.
Settlement instruction database information.
Information related to registration of securities.
Relates an amount to a period of time.
Plan that allows investors to schedule periodical investments or divestments, according to pre-defined criteria.
Preparation/bringing to market of a security (also known as primary market or Initial Public Offering (IPO) issuance).
Specifies the payment terms of the obligation.
Relates a percentage to a period of time.
Type of entity that plays a specific role in a specific context.
information about the periods of activity and non-activity of a system.
